00:12:27,310 --> 00:12:28,930
But then we missed a weekend away together,

264
00:12:28,980 --> 00:12:30,480
and things kind of unraveled...

265
00:12:31,210 --> 00:12:32,720
...because of you.

266
00:12:33,980 --> 00:12:35,300
Happy birthday.

267
00:12:36,780 --> 00:12:37,820
Ross, Rachel promised

268
00:12:37,820 --> 00:12:39,360
it would be over by now.

269
00:12:39,360 --> 00:12:40,900
We seriously have to go

270
00:12:40,900 --> 00:12:41,920
if we want to get to Vermont.

271
00:12:41,970 --> 00:12:43,180
I called them,

272
00:12:43,190 --> 00:12:44,400
the last train leaves in a half-hour.

273
00:12:44,450 --> 00:12:46,350
And I have a massage client soon.

274
00:12:46,400 --> 00:12:49,200
You guys, just, please, a little bit longer.

275
00:12:49,250 --> 00:12:50,110
I promise,

276
00:12:50,110 --> 00:12:51,840
Rachel will be back with the cake any minute.

277
00:12:51,890 --> 00:12:55,060
Monica, remember the frosting, huh?

278
00:12:55,720 --> 00:12:57,350
All right, five more minutes.

279
00:13:00,370 --> 00:13:01,460
Hello?

280
00:13:02,400 --> 00:13:03,840
Oh, no, what happened?

281
00:13:04,520 --> 00:13:06,780
Okay, okay, where are you?

282
00:13:07,240 --> 00:13:08,930
Okay, I'll be right there.

283
00:13:09,670 --> 00:13:10,550
Was that Emma?

284
00:13:10,550 --> 00:13:11,190
Is she up?

285
00:13:12,450 --> 00:13:14,590
Rachel got pulled over for speeding.

286
00:13:14,640 --> 00:13:16,090
She forgot her license.

287
00:13:16,090 --> 00:13:17,000
I have to bring it to her.

288
00:13:17,050 --> 00:13:19,420
If you're leaving, I'm definitely going.

289
00:13:19,470 --> 00:13:22,470
Wait, if anybody gets to go, it's us!

290
00:13:22,520 --> 00:13:24,420
We've been complaining the longest!

291
00:13:25,360 --> 00:13:27,940
No, wait, you guys. No, you can't leave.

292
00:13:27,990 --> 00:13:30,890
Rachel already feels bad that the cake's messed up.

293
00:13:30,940 --> 00:13:33,060
How do you think she'll feel

294
00:13:33,060 --> 00:13:34,040
when she comes back and you're gone?

295
00:13:34,090 --> 00:13:36,520
I don't know. You'll tell us on Monday.

296
00:13:38,210 --> 00:13:40,780
Joey, you're in charge, okay?

297
00:13:40,780 --> 00:13:41,950
You make sure nobody leaves.

298
00:13:42,000 --> 00:13:43,270
Got it!

299
00:13:45,390 --> 00:13:47,360
Hey! Where do you think you're going?

300
00:13:47,410 --> 00:13:48,920
To the bathroom.

301
00:13:48,970 --> 00:13:51,070
Well, the rest of you get comfortable,

302
00:13:51,120 --> 00:13:52,980
because we are gonna be here for a--

303
00:13:53,780 --> 00:13:55,270
Wait, there's a window in there.

304
00:13:55,320 --> 00:13:57,950
No! He's not getting away that easy!

305
00:13:59,870 --> 00:14:01,450
What are you doing?

306
00:14:01,450 --> 00:14:02,440
Get the hell out of here!

307
00:14:09,630 --> 00:14:11,760
Well, that one did not have Emma's face on it.

308
00:14:12,640 --> 00:14:14,340
- No, it did not. - No.

309
00:14:15,510 --> 00:14:17,900
Well, we'd better get going. It's late.

310
00:14:17,950 --> 00:14:19,760
Jack can't drive at night anymore.

311
00:14:19,760 --> 00:14:21,560
He has trouble staying in his lane.

312
00:14:21,610 --> 00:14:23,660
Last winter I went up on a church lawn

313
00:14:23,710 --> 00:14:25,700
and drove right through a manger scene.

314
00:14:25,750 --> 00:14:27,850
The papers thought it was a hate crime.

315
00:14:32,130 --> 00:14:34,630
- Anyway, it was lovely seeing you. - Okay.

316
00:14:34,680 --> 00:14:37,090
- Bye. Bye, dear. - Nighty-night.

317
00:14:37,140 --> 00:14:38,760
- Nighty-night. - Bye.

318
00:14:39,640 --> 00:14:41,430
How could you just let them leave?

319
00:14:41,430 --> 00:14:42,110
Hey, hey, hey.

320
00:14:42,110 --> 00:14:43,470
I'm not gonna mess with Jack.

321
00:14:43,520 --> 00:14:45,470
He's a great man. He fought for our country.

322
00:14:46,300 --> 00:14:47,430
No, he didn't.

323
00:14:47,430 --> 00:14:48,720
He pretended to be a Quaker

324
00:14:48,720 --> 00:14:49,850
to get out of Korea.

325
00:14:51,500 --> 00:14:54,210
Well, that's it. He's the last one to go.

326
00:14:54,210 --> 00:14:55,300
I'm locking you guys in.

327
00:14:56,350 --> 00:14:57,720
You do know I can just turn them

328
00:14:57,720 --> 00:14:59,090
the other way around, right?

329
00:15:00,240 --> 00:15:02,380
Oh, I forgot you used to live here.

330
00:15:07,830 --> 00:15:10,700
- Hello? - Joey, it's Estelle.

331
00:15:10,750 --> 00:15:14,080
- Hey. - So how'd your audition go today?

332
00:15:14,130 --> 00:15:15,500
What audition?

333
00:15:15,500 --> 00:15:17,640
The one I told you about last week.

334
00:15:17,690 --> 00:15:19,910
What? You never said anything about an audition.

335
00:15:23,520 --> 00:15:25,520
Let me start over.

336
00:15:25,530 --> 00:15:28,040
I just got a call about an audition.

337
00:15:28,880 --> 00:15:30,790
I think you can still make it.

338
00:15:30,840 --> 00:15:32,960
It's down at the Astor Theater,

339
00:15:33,010 --> 00:15:35,110
and you need to have a monologue prepared.

340
00:15:35,160 --> 00:15:37,300
A monologue? I don't have a--

341
00:15:41,080 --> 00:15:42,290
I got it.

342
00:15:44,170 --> 00:15:46,640
So I'm gonna take off.

343
00:15:46,690 --> 00:15:47,430
What?

344
00:15:47,430 --> 00:15:49,190
No, wait! You don't get to leave.

345
00:15:49,240 --> 00:15:52,460
I've got a massage client waiting outside my door any minute.

346
00:15:52,510 --> 00:15:54,500
And we paid for a room

347
00:15:54,500 --> 00:15:55,660
that we're supposed to be in right now!

348
00:15:55,710 --> 00:15:57,200
Well, okay, now...

349
00:15:57,600 --> 00:15:59,850
...only one of us has to stay with Emma.

350
00:16:00,790 --> 00:16:03,400
Okay, and as the person who realized that, I get to go.

351
00:16:03,920 --> 00:16:05,690
No...

352
00:16:05,900 --> 00:16:08,570
Let's figure out a fair way to decide who's staying.

353
00:16:08,850 --> 00:16:10,730
Oh, I got it.

354
00:16:11,050 --> 00:16:13,760
Okay, everyone pick a number from one to 10, all right?

355
00:16:13,810 --> 00:16:16,700
Whoever gets the highest number gets to go first.

356
00:16:19,110 --> 00:16:20,620
Okay, 10.

357
00:16:20,620 --> 00:16:21,580
Okay, Monica picks 10. I call nine.

358
00:16:21,630 --> 00:16:22,810
Anyone else?

359
00:16:24,320 --> 00:16:27,170
- No, let's just draw straws. - Okay.

360
00:16:27,220 --> 00:16:29,260
Or we could flip a coin and multiply the answer--

361
00:16:29,310 --> 00:16:31,680
- I'm begging you to stop. - Right.

362
00:16:32,270 --> 00:16:33,680
Okay, how about this?

363
00:16:33,780 --> 00:16:35,880
We got wind-up toys for Emma.

364
00:16:35,930 --> 00:16:37,030
We can make them race,

365
00:16:37,030 --> 00:16:39,420
and whoever comes in last stays.

366
00:16:39,470 --> 00:16:41,170
Yeah, let's do that!

367
00:16:42,050 --> 00:16:43,160
That sounds more fun than the thing

368
00:16:43,170 --> 00:16:44,760
we were gonna do in Vermont!

369
00:16:44,920 --> 00:16:47,570
Okay, everybody, pick your toys!

370
00:16:47,570 --> 00:16:48,900
Okay. I want the dolphin!

371
00:16:48,950 --> 00:16:51,120
- That's a bear! - I'm too excited!

372
00:16:52,680 --> 00:16:54,330
Phoebe, you get the bear.

373
00:16:54,330 --> 00:16:55,670
Joey, you get the robot.

374
00:16:55,720 --> 00:16:56,690
Oh, yeah.

375
00:16:56,690 --> 00:16:57,900
And Chandler and I get the dog.

376
00:16:57,950 --> 00:17:02,460
And the race is going to go from here to here.

377
00:17:02,510 --> 00:17:05,870
Now, the one who comes in last stays!

378
00:17:05,920 --> 00:17:07,250
Okay, ladies and gentlemen,

379
00:17:07,250 --> 00:17:08,130
wind your toys.

380
00:17:08,320 --> 00:17:11,650
Okay. On your mark, get set, go!

381
00:17:11,650 --> 00:17:12,760
Go! Go!

382
00:17:12,810 --> 00:17:14,460
Come on, robot!

383
00:17:16,340 --> 00:17:18,330
What are you barking at?

384
00:17:24,430 --> 00:17:26,600
Well, how is that gonna help?

385
00:17:27,090 --> 00:17:28,380
I bought you!

386
00:17:28,380 --> 00:17:30,740
How did I forget that that's all you do?

387
00:17:31,300 --> 00:17:33,550
Way to go, robot!

388
00:17:33,990 --> 00:17:35,640
Good job, Alan.

389
00:17:36,860 --> 00:17:38,030
Hey, good race, you guys.

390
00:17:38,030 --> 00:17:39,200
Yeah, see you later.

391
00:17:39,250 --> 00:17:41,420
No. No, no. Wait.

392
00:17:41,470 --> 00:17:43,200
We didn't lose.

393
00:17:43,450 --> 00:17:44,880
The rules clearly stated that

394
00:17:44,930 --> 00:17:47,890
the last one to cross the finish line was the loser.

395
00:17:47,940 --> 00:17:49,090
Well, our dog never crossed

396
00:17:49,090 --> 00:17:51,240
the finish line. So technically--

397
00:17:51,290 --> 00:17:52,430
They left.

398
00:17:58,530 --> 00:18:00,180
There isn't time to go to the bakery.

399
00:18:00,180 --> 00:18:01,820
We're gonna come home.

400
00:18:02,360 --> 00:18:04,070
Everybody left?

401
00:18:05,510 --> 00:18:06,680
All right. Well, just tell Emma

402
00:18:06,730 --> 00:18:09,570
that we'll be there as soon as we can. Bye.

403
00:18:11,380 --> 00:18:13,510
- Rachel! - Oh, God, sorry!

404
00:18:13,560 --> 00:18:15,040
I can't believe they gave you a ticket.

405
00:18:15,090 --> 00:18:16,510
You're such a good driver.

406
00:18:18,710 --> 00:18:21,580
- Emma's awake. - Yeah?

407
00:18:22,630 --> 00:18:24,100
I can't believe this.

408
00:18:24,150 --> 00:18:26,060
This is her first birthday,

409
00:18:26,060 --> 00:18:27,750
she's awake, we're not even there.

410
00:18:27,800 --> 00:18:29,470
Everybody left.

411
00:18:29,480 --> 00:18:31,150
We still have this stupid obscene cake.

412
00:18:31,200 --> 00:18:32,930
Hey, maybe I can fix that.

413
00:18:32,980 --> 00:18:35,090
You know, try to turn it into something else.

414
00:18:35,140 --> 00:18:37,550
Oh, don't even bother.

415
00:18:37,910 --> 00:18:40,070
We've already ruined her first birthday.

416
00:18:40,490 --> 00:18:41,050
And do you know

417
00:18:41,050 --> 00:18:43,010
how important these early experiences are,

418
00:18:43,060 --> 00:18:44,510
Ross? Very!

419
00:18:44,770 --> 00:18:47,400
According to the back cover of that book that you gave me.

420
00:18:49,040 --> 00:18:51,210
Rach, she's not gonna remember this.

421
00:18:53,080 --> 00:18:54,410
I guess.

422
00:18:55,470 --> 00:18:57,520
Oh, I just had such an idea

423
00:18:57,530 --> 00:19:00,600
of what this day would be like, you know?

424
00:19:01,270 --> 00:19:03,040
Emma laughing...

425
00:19:03,690 --> 00:19:05,690
...and everybody gathered around her cake,

426
00:19:05,690 --> 00:19:07,690
singing "Happy Birthday."

427
00:19:08,020 --> 00:19:09,090
And then we would all--

428
00:19:09,140 --> 00:19:11,390
Hey, get out of the road,

429
00:19:11,390 --> 00:19:12,140
you stupid student driver!

430
00:19:14,140 --> 00:19:15,680
They have to learn.

431
00:19:18,450 --> 00:19:19,830
- Hey. - What?

432
00:19:19,880 --> 00:19:21,220
This is not bad.

433
00:19:22,150 --> 00:19:23,660
Oh, my God. Look, you made it into a bunny.

434
00:19:23,660 --> 00:19:27,070
How did you do that?

435
00:19:27,120 --> 00:19:30,460
Well, I just made these two things cheeks.

436
00:19:32,230 --> 00:19:35,410
And then I split this to make ears.

437
00:19:36,310 --> 00:19:38,580
Well, I am very impressed.

438
00:19:38,850 --> 00:19:40,890
Some can sing, some can dance.

439
00:19:40,940 --> 00:19:42,030
I, apparently, can turn phallic cakes

440
00:19:42,030 --> 00:19:44,210
into woodland creatures.

441
00:19:46,640 --> 00:19:49,810
Now, another way to organize your stuffed animals

442
00:19:49,810 --> 00:19:51,080
is by size.

443
00:19:51,250 --> 00:19:53,350
I'm sorry, is this a game

444
00:19:53,350 --> 00:19:54,130
for Emma or for Monica?

445
00:19:55,690 --> 00:19:56,750
Game?

446
00:19:57,430 --> 00:20:00,700
Emma, do you even know it's your birthday today?

447
00:20:00,700 --> 00:20:01,790
You're 1.

448
00:20:02,040 --> 00:20:04,960
One year old. That's little.

449
00:20:07,760 --> 00:20:09,480
That's my girl.

450
00:20:10,770 --> 00:20:12,770
That's how old you are.

451
00:20:13,100 --> 00:20:14,930
Did I teach her that?

452
00:20:14,930 --> 00:20:16,540
Did I just impart wisdom?

453
00:20:19,230 --> 00:20:20,750
I want one.

454
00:20:22,130 --> 00:20:23,300
Me too.

455
00:20:28,960 --> 00:20:30,010
There's no one around.

456
00:20:30,010 --> 00:20:31,350
Why don't we just take this one?

457
00:20:32,860 --> 00:20:34,860
- And head to Canada. - I was kidding.

458
00:20:34,910 --> 00:20:36,660
I wasn't. Let's get going.

459
00:20:38,440 --> 00:20:40,730
Hey, are Ross and Rachel back?

460
00:20:40,730 --> 00:20:41,500
No, not yet.

461
00:20:41,550 --> 00:20:43,840
Oh, good, I didn't miss the party.

462
00:20:43,890 --> 00:20:45,470
What about your massage client?

463
00:20:45,520 --> 00:20:47,390
I just felt so bad missing this.

464
00:20:47,440 --> 00:20:49,600
So I just slipped him a little something, you know.

465
00:20:50,620 --> 00:20:52,580
As long as I'm back in five or six hours,

466
00:20:52,580 --> 00:20:53,570
it'll be all right.

467
00:20:55,850 --> 00:20:56,880
Okay.

468
00:20:57,460 --> 00:20:59,600
If Ross and Rachel ask,

469
00:20:59,610 --> 00:21:01,220
I've been here the whole time. The whole time.

470
00:21:02,580 --> 00:21:04,630
I've been here the whole time.

471
00:21:05,870 --> 00:21:07,510
Joey, we just saw you come in.

472
00:21:07,560 --> 00:21:09,700
You ran past us on the stairs.

473
00:21:10,840 --> 00:21:12,480
I don't care that you left.

474
00:21:12,530 --> 00:21:14,540
I'm just glad that you're here.

475
00:21:14,540 --> 00:21:15,160
Thanks, you guys.

476
00:21:15,210 --> 00:21:16,090
Hey, guys, come on.

477
00:21:16,090 --> 00:21:17,990
You gotta see what Emma just did.

478
00:21:18,040 --> 00:21:20,410
- What? - Emma, how old are you?

479
00:21:20,460 --> 00:21:22,370
How old are you today?

480
00:21:26,090 --> 00:21:29,330
Emma, that's right. You're that many.

481
00:21:29,380 --> 00:21:32,220
Oh, my God, our daughter's a genius.

482
00:21:33,210 --> 00:21:35,100
- This means-- - No! No science camp!

483
00:21:35,150 --> 00:21:39,480
Damn it! I'll put a candle on the cake.

484
00:21:40,210 --> 00:21:43,930
Oh, and, Emma, look at your stuffed animals

485
00:21:43,930 --> 00:21:45,790
lined up so neatly.

486
00:21:46,400 --> 00:21:47,470
Thanks.

487
00:21:48,540 --> 00:21:51,200
Okay, here we go.

488
00:21:51,970 --> 00:21:55,490
Emma's first birthday cake.

489
00:21:57,100 --> 00:21:58,730
Go ahead, Emma, blow out the candle.

490
00:21:59,270 --> 00:22:01,550
Come on, Emma. You can do it.

491
00:22:01,820 --> 00:22:03,550
What's wrong? Are you okay?

492
00:22:03,550 --> 00:22:04,420
Oh, yeah, nothing.

493
00:22:05,130 --> 00:22:06,970
These are happy tears.

494
00:22:07,860 --> 00:22:09,740
This is just what I wanted.

495
00:22:11,880 --> 00:22:13,750
Hey, you made it into a bunny.

496
00:22:15,280 --> 00:22:17,100
What is wrong with me?

497
00:22:17,150 --> 00:22:19,100
It looked more delicious when it was a penis.

498
00:22:26,040 --> 00:22:28,000
- Okay, you ready? - Yeah.

499
00:22:28,000 --> 00:22:30,860
- And record. - Okay.

500
00:22:31,300 --> 00:22:32,650
Hi, Emma.

501
00:22:32,830 --> 00:22:35,460
Well, your first birthday is over, and--

502
00:22:35,460 --> 00:22:36,940
Go! Go! Come on!

503
00:22:36,940 --> 00:22:38,760
Go! Go! Come on!

504
00:22:40,500 --> 00:22:45,270
Go! Go, Alan! Run, you hairy bastard!

